H3cQinQSwitchState.name: H3cQinQSwitchState
H3cQinQSwitchState.description: An enumerated value which indicates the state of switch.

h3cQinQBpduTunnelSwitch.name: h3cQinQBpduTunnelSwitch
h3cQinQBpduTunnelSwitch.description: The global configuration switch of BPDU 802.1q tunnel. If global configuration is disabled, BPDU tunnel function will be disabled despite of the corresponding configuration of interface. BPDU tunnel function of a certain interface would work only if the global and interface's switch are both enabled.

h3cQinQEthernetTypeValue.name: h3cQinQEthernetTypeValue
h3cQinQEthernetTypeValue.description: Ethernet protocol type configuring for a global value. The ethernet protocol type is also the TPID(Tag Protocol Identity) field of a VLAN tag described in 802.1q document. This value can be also configured for an individual interface or VLAN. The node that configure this value for a single interface is h3cQinQIfEthernetType, whose priority is higher than h3cQinQEthernetTypeValue. That means, if the value configured for a interface is different from the global value, the switch will select the configuration of the interface and ignore the global configuration. The ethernet protocol type of node h3cQinQVidEthernetType that configured for a VLAN has the highest priority.

h3cQinQServiceTPIDValue.name: h3cQinQServiceTPIDValue
h3cQinQServiceTPIDValue.description: Ethernet protocol type configured for service VLAN tags globally. The ethernet protocol type is also the TPID(Tag Protocol Identity) field of a VLAN tag described in 802.1q document. This value can be also configured for an individual interface. The node that configure this value for a single interface is h3cQinQIfServiceTPIDValue, whose priority is higher than h3cQinQServiceTPIDValue. That means, if the value configured for a interface is different from the global value, the switch will select the configuration of the interface and ignore the global configuration.

h3cQinQCustomerTPIDValue.name: h3cQinQCustomerTPIDValue
h3cQinQCustomerTPIDValue.description: Ethernet protocol type configured for customer VLAN tags globally. The ethernet protocol type is also the TPID(Tag Protocol Identity) field of a VLAN tag described in 802.1q document. This value can be also configured for an individual interface. The node that configure this value for a single interface is h3cQinQIfCustomerTPIDValue, whose priority is higher than h3cQinQCustomerTPIDValue. That means, if the value configured for a interface is different from the global value, the switch will select the configuration of the interface and ignore the global configuration.

h3cQinQBpduTunnelTable.name: h3cQinQBpduTunnelTable
h3cQinQBpduTunnelTable.description: A table for configuring 802.1q BPDU tunnel function for interfaces.

h3cQinQBpduTunnelEntry.name: h3cQinQBpduTunnelEntry
h3cQinQBpduTunnelEntry.description: An entry for configuring 802.1q BPDU tunnel function for interfaces.

h3cQinQProtocolIndex.name: h3cQinQProtocolIndex
h3cQinQProtocolIndex.description: The index of protocol on which the BPDU tunnel state will be set. 'bpdu' represents status of BPDU tunnel. 'stp' represents STP tunnel. 'gvrp' represents GVRP tunnel. 'igmp' represents IGMP tunnel. STP/GVRP/IGMP tunnel will start to work only if BPDU tunnel and STP/GVRP/IGMP tunnel are both enabled.

h3cQinQBpduRowStatus.name: h3cQinQBpduRowStatus
h3cQinQBpduRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

h3cQinQPriorityRemarkTable.name: h3cQinQPriorityRemarkTable
h3cQinQPriorityRemarkTable.description: A table for configuring priority field in 802.1Q-in-Q outer VLAN tag for interfaces. This feature uses the priority of an inner VLAN tag to remark the priority of an outer VLAN tag.

h3cQinQPriorityRemarkEntry.name: h3cQinQPriorityRemarkEntry
h3cQinQPriorityRemarkEntry.description: An entry for configuring priority remark function for interfaces.

h3cQinQPriorityValue.name: h3cQinQPriorityValue
h3cQinQPriorityValue.description: The priority value in inner VLAN tag. Since the priority range is from 0 to 7, yet the index range is from 1 to 8. Thus, the actual priority value equals to the value that subtracts 1 from corresponding index value.

h3cQinQPriorityRemarkValue.name: h3cQinQPriorityRemarkValue
h3cQinQPriorityRemarkValue.description: The new priority value used to fill outer tag.

h3cQinQPriorityRowStatus.name: h3cQinQPriorityRowStatus
h3cQinQPriorityRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

h3cQinQVidTable.name: h3cQinQVidTable
h3cQinQVidTable.description: A table for configuring VLAN ID of the 802.1Q-in-Q interfaces.

h3cQinQVidEntry.name: h3cQinQVidEntry
h3cQinQVidEntry.description: An entry for configuring VLAN ID of the 802.1Q-in-Q interfaces.

h3cQinQInboundVidListLow.name: h3cQinQInboundVidListLow
h3cQinQInboundVidListLow.description: The inbound VLAN IDs which need 802.1Q-in-Q processing. The VLAN ID range, described by bitmap, is from 1 to 2048. The length of bitmap is 256 in bytes. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN.

h3cQinQInboundVidListHigh.name: h3cQinQInboundVidListHigh
h3cQinQInboundVidListHigh.description: The inbound VLAN IDs which need 802.1Q-in-Q processing. The VLAN ID range, described by bitmap, is from 2049 to 4094. The length of bitmap is 256 in bytes. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN.

h3cQinQVidEthernetType.description: Ethernet protocol type configuring for a VLAN.

h3cQinQPrioritySwapTable.name: h3cQinQPrioritySwapTable
h3cQinQPrioritySwapTable.description: A table for configuring 802.1Q-in-Q inner VLAN priority swapping function for interfaces. Using this function, the priority of inner VLAN tag can be modified.

h3cQinQPrioritySwapEntry.name: h3cQinQPrioritySwapEntry
h3cQinQPrioritySwapEntry.description: An entry for configuring 802.1Q-in-Q inner VLAN priority swapping function for interfaces.

h3cQinQPrioritySwapOld.name: h3cQinQPrioritySwapOld
h3cQinQPrioritySwapOld.description: The old priority of original 802.1Q packets. It is the priority of inner VLAN tag. Since the VLAN priority range is from 0 to 7, yet the index range is from 1 to 8. Thus, the actual priority value equals to the value that subtracts 1 from corresponding index value.

h3cQinQPrioritySwapNew.name: h3cQinQPrioritySwapNew
h3cQinQPrioritySwapNew.description: The new priority of original 802.1Q packets. It is the priority of inner VLAN tag after swapped.

h3cQinQPrioritySwapRowStatus.name: h3cQinQPrioritySwapRowStatus
h3cQinQPrioritySwapRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.
